"{\"uid\": \"foxnews.com-live-news-olympics-2024-paris-august-10\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten, or redistributed.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 75, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a92026 FOX News Network, LLC.\", \"from\": 76, \"to\": 104, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 82, \"end\": 98, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"FOX News Network\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 105, \"to\": 125, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Quotes displayed in real-time or delayed by at least 15 minutes.\", \"from\": 126, \"to\": 190, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Market data provided byFactset.\", \"from\": 191, \"to\": 222, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Powered and implemented byFactSet Digital Solutions.Legal Statement.\", \"from\": 223, \"to\": 291, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mutual Fund and ETF data provided byRefinitiv Lipper.\", \"from\": 292, \"to\": 345, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 308, \"end\": 311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exchange-traded_fund\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.762529831632185e-42, \"text\": \"ETF\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exchange-traded_fund\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exchange-traded_fund\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The USWNT is looking to complete their comeback with a gold medal in Paris on Saturday, while the U.S. men's basketball team is hoping to retain their Olympic title in a final against France.\", \"from\": 347, \"to\": 538, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 351, \"end\": 356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USWNT\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 416, \"end\": 421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.966838059632809e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 445, \"end\": 449, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.056648049486818e-14, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 531, \"end\": 537, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999998183621012, \"rank\": 1.8163835753808684e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Covered by:Paulina DedajandJackson Thompson  Coverage for this event has ended.\", \"from\": 540, \"to\": 619, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 551, \"end\": 558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paulina_Rubio\", \"score\": 0.99992303801305, \"rank\": 7.695504683361294e-05, \"text\": \"Paulina\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paulina_Rubio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paulina_Rubio\"}, {\"begin\": 575, \"end\": 583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0230492016524909e-16, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After the Court of Arbitration for Sport ruled thatJordan Chiles scorein the women's floor exercise should have not been increased, the International Gymnastics Federation (FIG) hasadjusted the final scoreto reflect the ruling.\", \"from\": 623, \"to\": 850, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 759, \"end\": 800, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Gymnastics Federation (FIG)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\"}, {\"begin\": 759, \"end\": 800, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Gymnastics Federation (FIG)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chiles original score of 13.666 was reinstated and she was bumped back down to fifth place.\", \"from\": 852, \"to\": 943, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Romania's Ana Barbosa, who initially finished in third before an inquiry to increase Chiles' score was made, jumped back up to third place with a score 13.766.\", \"from\": 944, \"to\": 1103, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 944, \"end\": 951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999313813556, \"rank\": 6.843264072202776e-08, \"text\": \"Romania\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The announcement did not specify the status of Chiles' medal.\", \"from\": 1104, \"to\": 1165, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Golden State Warriors superstar Steph Curry hit four 3-point shots in the final two minutes and 11 seconds of the gold medal game against France to lead the U.S. to win 98-87.\", \"from\": 1167, \"to\": 1342, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1167, \"end\": 1188, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golden_State_Warriors\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.737883154085089e-60, \"text\": \"Golden State Warriors\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golden_State_Warriors\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golden_State_Warriors\"}, {\"begin\": 1199, \"end\": 1210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Curry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Steph Curry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Curry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Curry\"}, {\"begin\": 1305, \"end\": 1311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999998183621012, \"rank\": 1.8163835753808684e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For Curry, it is his first Olympic medal in his first Olympic appearance.\", \"from\": 1344, \"to\": 1417, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In total, Curry hit eight 3-point shots to account for all 24 of his points.\", \"from\": 1418, \"to\": 1494, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The first of Curry's clutch late 3-pointer shots had come when France had cut the lead to just three points.\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1604, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1559, \"end\": 1565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999998183621012, \"rank\": 1.8163835753808684e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From there, Curry did not miss a shot for the remainder of the game.\", \"from\": 1605, \"to\": 1673, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is the fifth straight gold medal for the U.S. in the Olympics and eighth in the last nine Olympics.\", \"from\": 1675, \"to\": 1777, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Noah Lyles posted a picture with a negative COVID-19 test with a caption that read \\\"Thank God, I am Covid free,\\\" on Saturday afternoon.\", \"from\": 1779, \"to\": 1914, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1779, \"end\": 1789, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 1869, \"end\": 1872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/God\", \"score\": 0.999947561907671, \"rank\": 4.113474775499013e-05, \"text\": \"God\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/God\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/God\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles finished third in the men's 200-meter final on Thursday despite being a heavy favorite, and after collapsing on the track and needing medical attention after the race, it was reported that Lyles tested positive for COVID-19 the day before the race.\", \"from\": 1916, \"to\": 2170, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2111, \"end\": 2116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9999995754743387, \"rank\": 4.2452554341608544e-07, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 2137, \"end\": 2145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"score\": 0.9999982563746665, \"rank\": 1.5763040233548894e-06, \"text\": \"COVID-19\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I woke up early, about 5 a.m. on Tuesday morning, and I was just feeling really horrible.\", \"from\": 2172, \"to\": 2262, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I knew it was more than being sore from the 100,\\\" Lyles told NBC.\", \"from\": 2263, \"to\": 2328, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2324, \"end\": 2327, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9043466800318907, \"rank\": 0.10574669800286259, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I'd definitely say it's taken its toll, for sure, but I have never been more proud of myself for being able to come out here and get a bronze medal.\", \"from\": 2329, \"to\": 2478, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Last Olympics, I was very disappointed.\", \"from\": 2479, \"to\": 2518, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This time, I could not be more proud.\\\"\", \"from\": 2519, \"to\": 2557, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles later announced on social media that his Paris Olympics were \\\"probably over\\\" and he pulled out of the men's 4x100 relay on Friday.\", \"from\": 2559, \"to\": 2695, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles' coach, Lance Brauman, said the 27-year-old track and field star clinched the bronze despite racing with a102-degree feveron Friday.\", \"from\": 2697, \"to\": 2835, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2697, \"end\": 2702, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9999995754743387, \"rank\": 4.2452554341608544e-07, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"LeBron James has led the U.S. to an eight-point halftime lead over Victor Wembanyama and France.\", \"from\": 2839, \"to\": 2935, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2839, \"end\": 2851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LeBron James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}, {\"begin\": 2906, \"end\": 2923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Wembanyama\", \"score\": 0.9999841253316324, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Victor Wembanyama\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Wembanyama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Wembanyama\"}, {\"begin\": 2928, \"end\": 2934, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999998183621012, \"rank\": 1.8163835753808684e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Devin Booker leads the U.S. with 13 points, James, at 39, has put up seven points and five rebounds.\", \"from\": 2937, \"to\": 3037, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2937, \"end\": 2949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Devin_Booker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.829540728729816e-40, \"text\": \"Devin Booker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Devin_Booker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Devin_Booker\"}, {\"begin\": 2981, \"end\": 2986, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 0.9999999435149236, \"rank\": 5.5797739797108594e-08, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wembanyama has 13 points while Guerschon Yabusele leads France with 15.\", \"from\": 3039, \"to\": 3110, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3070, \"end\": 3088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guerschon_Yabusele\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Guerschon Yabusele\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guerschon_Yabusele\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guerschon_Yabusele\"}, {\"begin\": 3095, \"end\": 3101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999998183621012, \"rank\": 1.8163835753808684e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yabusele hit a buzzer beater at the end of the half to cut the lead down from 10.\", \"from\": 3111, \"to\": 3192, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jordan Chiles' bronze medalin the women's floor exercise final is in jeopardy after the Court of Arbitration for Sport ruled that the judging panel at the event had improperly granted an inquiry that\\u00a0increased Chiles' score, which moved her into bronze medal position over Romania's Ana Barbosu.\", \"from\": 3196, \"to\": 3491, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3196, \"end\": 3209, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jordan Chiles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\"}, {\"begin\": 3469, \"end\": 3476, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999313813556, \"rank\": 6.843264072202776e-08, \"text\": \"Romania\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is now up to the International Gymnastics Federation (FIG) to decide who will get the medal.\", \"from\": 3493, \"to\": 3588, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3513, \"end\": 3554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Gymnastics Federation (FIG)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\"}, {\"begin\": 3513, \"end\": 3554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Gymnastics Federation (FIG)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Gymnastics_Federation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If Chiles is stripped of her bronze, she will become the third gymnast in history to have an Olympic medal stripped, and the first to have one stripped for not violating a rule.\", \"from\": 3590, \"to\": 3767, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The other two were China's Dong Fangxiao and Romania's Andreea R\\u0103ducan, both of whom lost their medals from the 2000 Sydney Olympics.\", \"from\": 3769, \"to\": 3902, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3788, \"end\": 3793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999886504157, \"rank\": 1.1349882320220904e-08, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3796, \"end\": 3809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dong_Fangxiao\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dong Fangxiao\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dong_Fangxiao\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dong_Fangxiao\"}, {\"begin\": 3814, \"end\": 3821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999313813556, \"rank\": 6.843264072202776e-08, \"text\": \"Romania\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3881, \"end\": 3901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2000_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3883998567658366e-26, \"text\": \"2000 Sydney Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2000_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2000_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"R\\u0103ducan's individual all-around gold medal was stripped after testing positive for a banned substance from cold-medicine pills given to her by a team doctor.\", \"from\": 3904, \"to\": 4061, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"China's team all-around bronze was stripped after it was discovered Dong was just 14 years old in Sydney, which is two years too young to compete.\", \"from\": 4062, \"to\": 4208, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4062, \"end\": 4067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999886504157, \"rank\": 1.1349882320220904e-08, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4160, \"end\": 4166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999962193186166, \"rank\": 3.780694559001141e-06, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"American high jumper Shelby McEwen had a chance to share the gold medal with New Zealand's Hamish Kerr in the men's high jump final.\", \"from\": 4210, \"to\": 4342, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4210, \"end\": 4218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999998929442939, \"rank\": 1.0704436705254447e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 4231, \"end\": 4244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelby_McEwen\", \"score\": 0.999997037059826, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shelby McEwen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelby_McEwen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelby_McEwen\"}, {\"begin\": 4287, \"end\": 4298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.6119679800455003, \"rank\": 0.4833539103790465, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4301, \"end\": 4312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamish_Kerr\", \"score\": 0.9999998928324261, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hamish Kerr\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamish_Kerr\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamish_Kerr\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They each failed three times at 2.38m after clearing 2.36m on their first attempts, but instead of splitting the gold, they went to a jump-off.\", \"from\": 4343, \"to\": 4486, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kerr emerged victorious in the jump-off victorious, and McEwan took silver.\", \"from\": 4488, \"to\": 4563, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is McEwan's first Olympic medal.\", \"from\": 4564, \"to\": 4599, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. won its 34th track and field of the Paris Olympics with gold in the 4x400 women's relay.\", \"from\": 4603, \"to\": 4700, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The team of Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone, Alexis Holmes, Gabby Thomas and Shamier Little went almost unchallenged for the gold medal, as it spent most of the race so far ahead of the competition that there was no one else even seen on screen when the NBC broadcast camera was focused on an American.\", \"from\": 4702, \"to\": 4998, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4714, \"end\": 4720, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999962193186166, \"rank\": 3.780694559001141e-06, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}, {\"begin\": 4748, \"end\": 4754, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\", \"score\": 0.9999995136632879, \"rank\": 4.863368221306653e-07, \"text\": \"Holmes\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\"}, {\"begin\": 4756, \"end\": 4768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4732493163706434e-17, 