": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. won gold in the men's 4x400 relay with an Olympic record with a 2:54.44.\", \"from\": 5187, \"to\": 5268, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Raj Benjamin closed out the record-breaking performance for the U.S. just one day after winning an individual gold in the men's 400-meter hurdle.\", \"from\": 5269, \"to\": 5414, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Benjamin outran Botswana's gold medalist Letsile Tebogo, who defeated Noah Lyles for the gold medal in the men's 200-meter final, on the final leg to clinch victory.\", \"from\": 5416, \"to\": 5581, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5416, \"end\": 5424, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tribe_of_Benjamin\", \"score\": 0.9026249495383023, \"rank\": 0.05778132726850213, \"text\": \"Benjamin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tribe_of_Benjamin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tribe_of_Benjamin\"}, {\"begin\": 5432, \"end\": 5440, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.737844113439622, \"rank\": 0.3552998279436915, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}, {\"begin\": 5486, \"end\": 5496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For Benjamin, it is his second gold medal of the Tokyo Olympics.\", \"from\": 5583, \"to\": 5647, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5587, \"end\": 5595, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tribe_of_Benjamin\", \"score\": 0.9026249495383023, \"rank\": 0.05778132726850213, \"text\": \"Benjamin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tribe_of_Benjamin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tribe_of_Benjamin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the U.S., it marks a victory over Tebogo, who took asubtle dig at Lyles, after he was asked about becoming the face of men's track following his victory in the 200-meter final on Thursday.\", \"from\": 5649, \"to\": 5841, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5719, \"end\": 5724, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9999995754743387, \"rank\": 4.2452554341608544e-07, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tebogo suggested that Lyles was \\\"arrogant\\\" and \\\"loud\\\" after the 200-meter final, which Lyles won bronze in after testing positive for covid and having a102-degree fever.\", \"from\": 5842, \"to\": 6011, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5864, \"end\": 5869, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9999995754743387, \"rank\": 4.2452554341608544e-07, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 5929, \"end\": 5934, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9999995754743387, \"rank\": 4.2452554341608544e-07, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trey_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"American gymnastJordan Chiles may loseher\\u00a0Olympic bronze medal after the Court of Arbitration for Sport ruled that the judging panel at the event had improperly granted an inquiry that\\u00a0increased Chiles' score, which moved her into bronze medal position over Romania's Ana Barbosu.\", \"from\": 6015, \"to\": 6295, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6015, \"end\": 6023, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999998929442939, \"rank\": 1.0704436705254447e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 6273, \"end\": 6280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999313813556, \"rank\": 6.843264072202776e-08, \"text\": \"Romania\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Barbosu initially clinched the bronze medal for floor on Monday and began celebrating on the mat.\", \"from\": 6297, \"to\": 6394, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But then U.S. coaches appealed to judges over Chiles' score, and a review resulted in a 0.1-point increase, which moved Chiles ahead of Barbosu for the bronze medal.\", \"from\": 6395, \"to\": 6560, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Court of Arbitration has now said that Chiles should have received a score of 13.666 in the event, which would have placed her fifth, just shy of the Olympic podium.\", \"from\": 6562, \"to\": 6731, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Chiles posted a series of emotional stories on Instagram Saturday in response to the ruling, including one that showed a series of broken heart emojis, and another that included her announcement that she would be leaving social media.\", \"from\": 6733, \"to\": 6967, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am taking this time and removing myself from social media for my mental health,\\\" Chiles wrote.\", \"from\": 6969, \"to\": 7066, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In just hissecond Olympics,Grant Fisher has made history in Paris.\", \"from\": 7070, \"to\": 7136, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7097, \"end\": 7109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grant_Fisher\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Grant Fisher\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grant_Fisher\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grant_Fisher\"}, {\"begin\": 7130, \"end\": 7135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.966838059632809e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The American long distance runner secured a bronze medal in the men's 5,000-meter final on Saturday, finishing behind Jakob Ingebrigtsen of Norway, who won the gold medal with a season best of 13:13.66.\", \"from\": 7138, \"to\": 7340, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7142, \"end\": 7150, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999998929442939, \"rank\": 1.0704436705254447e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 7256, \"end\": 7274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jakob Ingebrigtsen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\"}, {\"begin\": 7278, \"end\": 7284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999745341, \"rank\": 2.5098880740149165e-11, \"text\": \"Norway\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was Fisher's second medal of these Games - he stunned the field in the men's 10,000-meter final to win bronze.\", \"from\": 7342, \"to\": 7455, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7349, \"end\": 7355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Derek_Fisher\", \"score\": 0.999999996914994, \"rank\": 3.085018375475573e-09, \"text\": \"Fisher\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Derek_Fisher\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Derek_Fisher\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is the first time an American has ever medaled in both events.\", \"from\": 7456, \"to\": 7521, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7480, \"end\": 7488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999998929442939, \"rank\": 1.0704436705254447e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fisher improved on his Olympic debut in Tokyo where he was a finalist in both events, but failed to medal.\", \"from\": 7523, \"to\": 7629, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7563, \"end\": 7568, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999667360974047, \"rank\": 3.326500945481034e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"American Masai Russell is anOlympic championafter pulling off a narrow victory in the women's 100-meter hurdles final on Saturday, beating out France's Cyrena Samba-Mayela by one one-hundredths of a second.\", \"from\": 7631, \"to\": 7837, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7631, \"end\": 7639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999998929442939, \"rank\": 1.0704436705254447e-07, \"text\":